Subject: [PATCH] Add complete documentation page at /doc
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A single, thorough docs page covering the whole product so users
understand it before billing conversations start:
- Overview of the Greenfield vs Brownfield workflows
- Creating an account & signing in (org-email requirement,
  verification, password reset)
- Dashboard walkthrough (stat cards, recent blueprints, recent
  brownfield migrations, activity)
- Greenfield: the Gatekeeper/Architect/Engineer/Auditor pipeline,
  and all 5 blueprint steps (Infra design, Security, Cost, DR,
  Review & export)
- Brownfield: input types, the Scanner/Auditor/Planner/Engineer
  pipeline, and all 5 migration steps (Overview, Audit findings,
  Migration plan, Terraform output, Review & export) — noted as
  Team plan & up
- Knowledge Base — what it does and why it matters
- Plans & features table (Scout/Pro/Team/Enterprise), matching
  the figures already on the public pricing section exactly
- Settings & account overview
- FAQ, including the cost-estimate and verify-before-deploy
  disclaimers, linking to /terms

Also:
- lib/supabase/middleware.ts: added /doc to the isPublic allowlist
  (same gap as /terms and /privacy previously) so it's readable
  without signing in
- public/landing.html: added a 'Docs' link to both the top nav
  and the footer Product column so it's actually discoverable
- app/dashboard/page.tsx: added a 'Docs' nav item in the sidebar
  Configuration section for logged-in users

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (23/23 pages,
new /doc route confirmed static in route table), no new lint
issues (the one error in dashboard/page.tsx is the same pre-existing
no-html-link-for-pages convention already present throughout this
codebase, confirmed via diff — unrelated to this change).
